==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''impolitus'', not polite.

===Adjective===
'''impolite''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')
# Not [[polite]]; not of polished manners; wanting in good manners.

====Synonyms====
*[[discourteous]], [[uncivil]], [[rude]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[epäkohtelias]]
*French: [[mal]] [[polit]]

===Adverb===
'''impolitely'''

===Noun===
'''impoliteness'''

